## Positioning Framework Selection

### Which Framework Should You Use?

**Use Classic Positioning When:**
- [ ] Category already exists (CRM, project management, etc.)
- [ ] Customers know they need this type of solution
- [ ] You're replacing an existing tool/process
- [ ] Clear competitive set (you know who you compete against)
- [ ] Differentiation is HOW you do it (faster, easier, cheaper)

**Use Pain-focused Positioning When:**
- [ ] Category doesn't exist or customers don't recognize it
- [ ] Customers have a pain but no solution awareness
- [ ] You're changing behavior, not just replacing a tool
- [ ] Differentiation is WHAT problem you solve
- [ ] Customers self-identify by problem, not by tool category

**Example Decision:**
- Slack (early days): Pain-focused - "solving email overload" (no "team chat" category existed)
- Slack (mature): Classic - "Against-the-Leader vs Microsoft Teams" (category established)

**Your Choice:** [Classic or Pain-focused]

